Preconditions:
The method `uncommonFromSentences` takes two parameters `s1` and `s2`, which are sentences.
The sentences `s1` and `s2` are not null.
The sentences `s1` and `s2` may contain words separated by spaces.
The sentences `s1` and `s2` may contain punctuation marks.
The sentences `s1` and `s2` may contain uppercase and lowercase letters.

Postconditions:
The method `uncommonFromSentences` returns a list of all the uncommon words.
The uncommon words are words that appear in either `s1` or `s2`, but not in both.
The uncommon words are returned in any order.
The returned list does not contain any duplicate words.
The returned list is of type `String[]`.